WEBVTT

00:07.220 --> 00:07.860
- Previously on "Happy"...

00:08.690 --> 00:10.190
- You're not real.

00:10.230 --> 00:12.600
- I'm Hailey's imaginary friend.

00:12.630 --> 00:14.630
- I have never seen
a room of young faces

00:14.660 --> 00:18.140
in such dire need of correction.

00:18.170 --> 00:21.170
- I need to know
who killed my Mikey.

00:21.210 --> 00:23.140
- You have an enemy
in your house.

00:23.170 --> 00:25.210
who killed your son.

00:25.240 --> 00:28.280
Mikey is not with them.

00:28.310 --> 00:30.210
Hey, Amanda.

00:30.250 --> 00:31.680
She's my daughter.

00:31.720 --> 00:33.250
- Look at the dumpster fire
that your life has become,

00:33.280 --> 00:36.120
and ask yourself how
I could rely on you.

00:36.150 --> 00:38.190
Get out.

00:38.220 --> 00:39.690
- What're you doing?
Get off the tracks.

00:39.720 --> 00:41.490
- You were the one with her
when she was kidnapped.

00:41.530 --> 00:43.130
- If you want me to go, fine.

00:43.160 --> 00:45.630
- Music to my ears, bye-bye.

00:45.660 --> 00:46.660
- Good-bye, partner.

00:48.370 --> 00:50.300
- Happy.

00:50.330 --> 00:52.470
Ah shit, I killed my kid's
imaginary friend.

00:52.500 --> 00:56.510
- She's one of my best men.

00:56.540 --> 00:58.440
- Blue!

00:58.480 --> 00:59.480
- Blue?

01:01.350 --> 01:03.410
- Shit's just getting
weirder and weirder.

01:04.709 --> 01:07.350
- My name is Happy.

01:07.380 --> 01:09.550
I'm an imaginary friend.

01:09.590 --> 01:12.620
And... no one believes in me.

01:12.660 --> 01:14.620
We believe in you.

01:14.660 --> 01:17.260
- Sorry, I just...

01:17.290 --> 01:19.630
I never thought I'd end up
somewhere like this.

01:19.660 --> 01:21.200
No offense.

01:21.230 --> 01:23.170
- None of us did, little fellow.

01:23.200 --> 01:26.700
The thing to remember is...
this wasn't your fault.

01:26.740 --> 01:30.740
- Right, well, that's nice.
You're all very nice.

01:30.770 --> 01:32.380
But it is my fault.

01:32.410 --> 01:35.350
She believed in me
and I failed, I...

01:35.380 --> 01:38.480
Look at me,
I'm fading away, I...

01:38.520 --> 01:40.350
My color, my coat.

01:40.380 --> 01:43.520
I used to be as blue as a
blueberry snow cone and now I...

01:43.550 --> 01:45.520
- You're still very blue.

01:45.560 --> 01:49.560
- Ah, there are millions of IFs
out there just like you, Happy.

01:49.590 --> 01:51.730
- Waiting for the moment
our young friends

01:51.760 --> 01:54.260
stop believing completely.

01:54.300 --> 01:56.730
- And we blink out of existence.

01:56.770 --> 01:59.770
- I knew this day would come,
I just...

01:59.800 --> 02:02.240
I didn't think it
would be so soon.

02:02.270 --> 02:05.680
- We have to learn to let go,
whenever they let go.

02:05.710 --> 02:08.680
- That's what it means
to be an IF.

02:08.710 --> 02:13.250
- Now or later,
we're destined for nothingness.

02:13.280 --> 02:15.520
- There's so much more for
Hailey and I to do.

02:15.550 --> 02:17.820
There's so many games, I...

02:17.850 --> 02:20.590
Aw.
Her first date.

02:20.620 --> 02:22.190
- Hah!
- Peep.

02:22.230 --> 02:23.690
Something you'd like to share?

02:23.730 --> 02:25.360
- Why, yes.

02:25.400 --> 02:29.570
It's not monsters under
the bed; it's penises.

02:29.600 --> 02:33.640
Great, big, nasty penises.

02:33.670 --> 02:36.370
Also, fuck Judy Blume.

02:36.410 --> 02:39.540
Two weeks with those books,
now my friend's knocked up

02:39.580 --> 02:42.310
and her water's breaking
in Algebra I.

02:45.750 --> 02:48.750
- Was it "Freckle Juice"?

02:52.720 --> 02:54.660
- Hello, friend.

02:54.690 --> 02:58.260
- Just one marshmallow?
They're free, you know.

02:58.300 --> 02:59.630
- I only deserve one.

02:59.660 --> 03:02.270
And only because it's not
hot chocolate without it.

03:02.300 --> 03:05.740
- You know, you showed real
vulnerability in there.

03:05.770 --> 03:08.510
I'm proud of you.
- Smoke?

03:08.540 --> 03:11.780
- After all the cocaine I had
this week, I don't think so.

03:12.740 --> 03:14.610
- Well, don't look so glum.

03:14.640 --> 03:17.480
The world is losing
its imagination, Happy.

03:17.510 --> 03:20.750
There were times I felt
we were all that's left.

03:20.780 --> 03:22.890
A dying breed.

03:22.920 --> 03:25.460
But then, I found a new friend.

03:25.490 --> 03:27.460
- A... a new friend?

03:27.490 --> 03:30.760
- Yep, with enough belief
for a hundred of us.

03:30.790 --> 03:34.600
- You're not, like, one of
those guys in the bowties

03:34.630 --> 03:36.370
that rings the doorbell,
are you?

03:36.400 --> 03:39.470
- Not at all.

03:39.500 --> 03:42.740
I can't promise you sweeter
pastures than the hereafter.

03:42.770 --> 03:46.780
But I will say, if you need
some warm straw to sleep on,

03:46.810 --> 03:48.350
so to speak,

03:48.380 --> 03:49.910
you're welcome to stay with us

03:49.950 --> 03:52.450
till you get back
on your hooves.

03:52.480 --> 03:54.450
- Oh, I couldn't intrude.

03:54.480 --> 03:56.790
- Nonsense.
No trouble at all.

03:56.820 --> 03:59.790
- That is, unless you got
somewhere better to go.

04:02.760 --> 04:04.330
- God damn it, they say that
if the bullet don't get you,

04:04.360 --> 04:05.600
